excerpt: 1 of 2 theme parks forming Disneyland Paris, with 'production zones' of TV/movie-linked attractions.
detail_description: Parc Walt Disney Studios is one of the two theme parks that make up Disneyland Paris, featuring areas dedicated to movie and TV related attractions. It may not be as large as the main park, however it offers rides more suitable for younger children such as the popular Cars ride. The Hollywood Tower and Ratatouille are considered to be two of the main attractions in this park, which boasts a beautiful setting and aims to create an atmosphere reminiscent of Walt Disney's production studios.
name: Parc Walt Disney Studios
address: Pl. des Frères Lumière, 77700 Chessy, France

excerpt: Popular retail complex with 2 floors of brand-name shops & eateries, plus an aquarium & health club.
name: Centre Commercial Val d'Europe
address: 3 Cr de la Garonne, 77700 Serris, France

excerpt: Family-friendly exhibits with a variety of sea creatures (most offer play areas & group packages).
detail_description: SEA LIFE Val d'Europe is a family-friendly destination showcasing an array of sea creatures. With group packages and play areas available, it offers an enjoyable experience for all ages. Visitors can witness penguins and rays being fed while exploring the well-planned layout that is easy to navigate. The aquarium features a variety of exhibits including informative talks on seahorses by knowledgeable staff members.
name: SEA LIFE Val d'Europe
address: Ccial Val d'Europe, 14 Cr du Danube, 77700 Serris, France

detail_description: The Enigmatic Live Escape Game in Marne-la-Vallée offers a Time Machine game where participants can have an amazing time solving fun riddles and escaping just in time. It's worth noting that this particular game is only available in French, so being at least at an intermediate level is necessary to fully enjoy it. The center itself boasts an impressive decoration and maintenance, with helpful and welcoming staff who offer well-thought-out activities.
name: ENIGMATIC LIVE ESCAPE GAME MARNE-LA-VALLÉE
address: 4 Av. James de Rothschild, 77164 Ferrières-en-Brie, France

detail_description: Mind Trap Live Escape Game 77 offers an exhilarating experience for groups looking to bond and have fun. Whether you're celebrating a bachelorette party or enjoying a team-building outing, the venue features three distinct rooms—Gentleman Agency, Magic Academy, and Mine of Secrets—each with its own unique atmosphere and engaging storylines. Guests rave about the immersive decor and well-crafted puzzles that challenge your creativity and teamwork. The friendly staff enhances the experience by providing excellent guidance throughout your adventure.
name: Mind Trap Live Escape Game 77

excerpt: Grand 1800s Renaissance-style château with ornate interiors, a parkland garden & upscale eateries.
detail_description: The Château de Ferrières is a stunning Renaissance-style castle located near Paris that offers luxurious interiors and beautiful parkland gardens. This event planner is perfect for hosting upscale events or receptions, with its grand atmosphere and picturesque surroundings. In addition to the elegant dining options available, the venue also offers enjoyable Sunday morning brunches that can be enjoyed on sunny days followed by a leisurely stroll in the gardens. Overall, this charming château provides a wonderful setting for any type of occasion.
name: Château de Ferrières

excerpt: Theme park complex featuring family-friendly rides, shows and costumed characters, plus hotels.
detail_description: Located near Paris in Marne-la-Vallee, Disneyland Paris is a renowned theme park complex that offers an enchanting and magical experience for visitors of all ages. Despite initial skepticism from the French, it has become the most successful theme park in Europe. The park features iconic attractions that bring beloved movies and cartoons to life, as well as thrilling rides for those seeking an adrenaline rush.
name: Disneyland Paris

excerpt: Sprawling recreational area with a lakeside beach, paddle boats, canoeing & simple eateries.
detail_description: Island Recreation Vaires-Torcy is a large recreational area with a lakeside beach, paddle boats, canoeing, and food outlets. However, accessing the attraction by foot can be unsafe due to the lack of proper walkways from the nearest village. The entrance to the attraction via a narrow two-lane carriageway is not well-maintained and disgustingly littered with human excrements.
name: Island Recreation Vaires - Torcy

detail_description: I had an incredible experience with a circle of companions at the unsettling house-themed game! The genuine embellishments and effectively coordinated riddle-solving exercises made for a delightful time. It was an extraordinary event loaded up with amusement that I would energetically prescribe to anybody. This escape room center, Escape Time Orléans - Escape game, offers a superb break from reality.
name: Escape Time Orléans - Escape game
address: 50 Rue de la Batardière, 45140 Saint-Jean-de-la-Ruelle, France

detail_description: An enjoyable and exciting time was spent at the GPark laser tag center, which offers a wide range of activities such as Laser Game, Escape Rooms, Virtual Reality experiences, Quiz Games, and the thrilling F1 Simulator. Both beginners and experienced participants can indulge in the realistic sensations provided by these various attractions. The professional and friendly staff ensure a warm welcome to all visitors.
name: GPark Orléans - Laser Game. Escape Game. Quiz Game. Karaoké. Simulateur F1. Mini Golf.
address: All. de l'Orée de la Forêt, 45770 Saran, France

detail_description: Jump City Trampoline Parc 77 is a small but well-equipped trampoline park with various attractions such as an airbag, foam pit, Ninja Parcours, and fighting lanes above the foam pit. The staff is friendly and provides a warm-up session before visitors can enjoy the new trampolines. It's described as a great place for kids to have fun and release energy while enjoying clean facilities and great music.
name: Jump City Trampoline Parc 77

detail_description: Parc des Communes is a delightful green space that invites visitors to unwind and connect with nature. This park features beautifully landscaped gardens, walking paths, and areas perfect for picnics or leisurely strolls. Families can enjoy the playgrounds while fitness enthusiasts appreciate the jogging trails.
name: Parc des Communes

detail_description: Château de Jossigny has been transformed into a vibrant community space, offering various activities and events to preserve its heritage and fund its maintenance. The castle is now open to the public, providing opportunities for locals to engage in cultural experiences. Although the main castle is currently closed due to its condition, visitors can still enjoy the beautiful kitchen and participate in storytelling sessions.
name: Château de Jossigny

excerpt: Neo-Renaissance administrative building with regular exhibitions & tours by appointment.
detail_description: Hôtel de Ville, also known as the Paris City Hall building, is a stunning Neo-Renaissance administrative building located between the Notre-Dame Cathedral and the Centre Pompidou. It is renowned for its remarkable facade adorned with statues of famous French historical figures. The building offers regular exhibitions and tours by appointment, providing visitors with an opportunity to explore its grandeur.
name: Hôtel de Ville

excerpt: Early 18th-century country house with lavish, rococo decor & antiquities, plus ornamental gardens.
detail_description: Château de Champs-sur-Marne is an early 18th-century country house located in a charming suburb of Paris. The architect Jean-Baptiste Bullet de Chamblain designed this lavish residence, which features rococo decor and ornamental gardens. Originally built for a financier, the estate has a rich history involving various owners and extensive decorative work. Visitors can explore the beautifully maintained gardens and the well-preserved manor house, which offers a glimpse into its interesting past.
name: Château de Champs-sur-Marne

detail_description: Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs ride is a popular attraction at various Disney parks. It offers a nostalgic experience for frequent visitors, with attention to detail that even adults can appreciate. The ride provides a retelling of the classic story through animatronics and light shows, making it suitable for all ages. While some find it quick, others believe it's worth the wait, although it may be slightly scary for young children.
name: Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs

detail_description: Lavoir is a charming and historic place that offers visitors a unique experience. It is described as an atmospheric spot with beautiful architecture and a tranquil ambiance. Visitors can immerse themselves in the rich history of Lavoir while enjoying its picturesque surroundings. The site is known for its cultural significance and architectural beauty, making it a must-visit for history enthusiasts and architecture lovers alike. Whether exploring the intricate design or simply taking in the serene atmosphere, Lavoir provides an unforgettable experience for all who visit.
name: Lavoir
address: 14 Rue de la Planchette, 89190 Flacy, France

detail_description: 3dSculptr.net is a website that offers 3D printing and sculpting services. They provide a platform for users to create, customize, and print their own 3D designs. The site features a user-friendly interface and a wide range of design options to choose from. With 3dSculptr.net, customers can bring their ideas to life through the power of 3D printing technology.
name: 3dSculptr.net

detail_description: Parc des Frênes is a stunning park offering breathtaking views and a serene atmosphere. It's beloved by many for its natural beauty and tranquil surroundings, making it a must-visit destination for nature enthusiasts.
name: Parc des Frênes
